Small Question Before We Start

Suppose:

class Animal {

    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Animal");
    }

}

class Dog extends Animal {

    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Dog");
    }

}

class Cat extends Animal {

    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Cat");
    }

}

Question:

If I have:

Animal a;

Can a become:

Dog?
Cat?

🤔

Just answer:

YES or NO.

Don't overthink it.

This answer is the key to understanding Polymorphism. 😎🔥

no

😄 Good guess, bro!

But the correct answer is:

✅ YES

And this is exactly why Polymorphism exists.

Don't worry. I'll explain it in ELI10 style.

Imagine Your Father 👨

Your father says:

"Bring an Animal."

What can you bring?

🐶 Dog?

✅ Yes

🐱 Cat?

✅ Yes

🦁 Lion?

✅ Yes

Because:

Dog IS AN Animal

Cat IS AN Animal

Lion IS AN Animal

This is called an IS-A relationship.

